  "prompt": "What Pok\u00e9mon hatches from Eggs in Pok\u00e9mon GO?",
  "response": "In Pok\u00e9mon GO, a variety of Pok\u00e9mon can hatch from Eggs. The Pok\u00e9mon you can get from hatching Eggs depends on the distance required to hatch them (2 km, 5 km, 7 km, 10 km, and 12 km). Here\u2019s a list of some Pok\u00e9mon that can hatch from each type of Egg as of my last update:\n\n### 2 km Eggs:\n- Pichu\n- Togepi\n- Cleffa\n- Igglybuff\n- Azurill\n- Happiny\n- Spritzee\n- Swirlix\n- Munchlax\n\n### 5 km Eggs:\n- Machop\n- Ponyta\n- Slowpoke\n- Geodude\n- Magikarp\n- Meditite\n- Wailmer\n- Buizel\n- Buneary\n- Woobat\n- Ferroseed\n- Klink\n- Litwick\n- Espurr\n\n### 7 km Eggs (obtained from Gifts):\n- Alolan Sandshrew\n- Alolan Vulpix\n- Alolan Diglett\n- Alolan Meowth\n- Alolan Geodude\n- Galarian Meowth\n- Galarian Ponyta\n- Galarian Slowpoke\n- Galarian Zigzagoon\n- Galarian Darumaka\n- Galarian Stunfisk\n\n### 10 km Eggs:\n- Bagon\n- Beldum\n- Dratini\n- Deino\n- Gible\n- Larvitar\n- Riolu\n- Shinx\n- Tirtouga\n- Archen\n- Goomy\n- Turtonator\n- Jangmo-o\n\n### 12 km Eggs (obtained from Team GO Rocket):\n- Pawniard\n- Vullaby\n- Deino\n- Pancham\n- Larvitar\n- Absol\n- Skorupi\n- Sandile\n- Scraggy\n- Salandit\n- Qwilfish\n- Bruxish\n\nPlease note that the list of Pok\u00e9mon that can hatch from Eggs can change with updates to the game, including events and seasons that might introduce new Pok\u00e9mon or change the Egg pools. Always check the latest in-game information or official updates from Niantic for the most current list of hatchable Pok\u00e9mon.",
